Commit: 74de25569deb8e99f1a6c141ce20625094ea8332

Build the following CCI using the 'chaintool build' command.
{code:java}
message Foo {}

message Bar {

    // Remove this comment to fix the build bug
    Foo my_foo = 1;

}
{code}
 

Expected: The CCI should build succeed.

Actual: The build fails with
{code:java}
Build using configuration for  ./
[CCI] parse bug
Error: Errors parsing /Users/sheehan/dev/temp/cciBug/src/interfaces/bug.cci: line 6: type "nt" for field "my_foo" is not defined
{code}
 

If the comment is removed, the build will succeed. This only seems to be an issue if the comment is above a composite type field. If the comment is above a scalar type field, the build is successful.

